{
  "texts": [
    "To encourage agents to learn coordination, they developed hot supervision contrastive loss derived from an expert planner, which was combined with the RL loss function for the policy network.",
    "This combined loss function facilitated the agents' learning of effective coordination strategies.",
    "Taking advantage of initializing the learning process of DRL agents with prior knowledge about the environment dynamics, Guo et al. (2020) also demonstrated improved decisionmaking capabilities and faster convergence by incorporating the artificial potential field (APF) into DDPG algorithm.",
    "For mapless navigation, Hu et al. (2020) integrated DDPG with Prioritised Experience Replay (PER), leading to faster convergence, reduced fluctuation, and the generation of safer and smoother trajectories.",
    "However, as mentioned in the previous section, these approaches cannot fully address the issues coming from partial observability, particularly in high-scaled long-range planning problems."
  ]
}